Let $p(n) = n^2 - n + 41$ and $p(n+1) = (n+1)^2 - (n+1) + 41$. We have

\begin{align*}
p(n+1) - p(n) &= (n+1)^2 - (n+1) + 41 - (n^2 - n + 41) \\
&= 2n + 1.
\end{align*}

If $p(n)$ and $p(n+1)$ share a common factor greater than $1$, then $2n+1$ must be a multiple of $p(n)$. Since $p(n)$ is prime, $2n+1$ must be equal to $p(n)$

